==Trivia== 

* ''RESONARK'' is also available as a standalone game on [https://store.steampowered.com/app/1366570/RESONARK_X/ Steam as '''RESONARK X'''], however it has not been updated to include songs from ''RESONARK 4: ELVES''. 
** A standalone Meta Quest version of the is also available, aptly named [https://www.meta.com/experiences/resonark-x-lite/3405379359561787/ '''RESONARK X LITE'''].
** The Standalone and Quest version, as of today, currenttly has no future plans to update their respective versions to include the context past Resonark 3.
*The sound design for ''RESONARK 4 -ELVES-'' was partially comprised by Tatsh, who was a notable artist within the BEMANI franchise, which was responsible for the DanceDanceRevolution and beatmaniaIIDX series. 
**Songs by NAOKI, another former BEMANI name, can also be found scattered across the franchises before his departure from KONAMI in 2014.
*Several other artists found within RESONARK can be found in other rhythm games, most notably having their start within BMS rhythm game events.
**HAGANE's "DDD" was originally a BMS OF FIGHTERS XVII -VISION THE RETRO FUTURE- song before it made its way to Arcaea and ''RESONARK 4: ELVES''
**ak+q's "Ignotus" originates from Arcaea.
**Tanchiky's "ENERGY SYNERGY MATRIX" came from BMS OF FIGHTERS 2017 before making its way onto several other rhythm games.
**onoken originally made BMS entries before appearing in beatmaniaIIDX.
***felys' [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2YGL7HNKk8M original version] was actually one of their entries submitted to a BMS event in 2002. The "final remix" version also appears in EZ2ON R: Reboot
*Maozon is a present name within the BEMANI franchise, while also having appeared in other rhythm game projects such as NAOKi's defunt "SEVEN's CODE"
*Nhato is another name present within BEMANI, but has expanded to other parts of doujin releases in recent years
**He also has made an arrangement of the final boss theme for the 2023 M2ShotTriggers Remaster of CAVE's shmup "DoDonPachi DAI-OU-JOU
*REDRAVE by Tatsh & NAOKI is a sequel to RED ZONE<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=19RLQFp_-A4 </ref>, originating from beatmaniaIIDX 11: IIDXRED''.''
*BRAIN POWER by NOMA can be found in several other rhythm games, such as SOUND VOLTEX, Groove Coaster, Pump It Up, NeonFM and SUPERBEAT XONiC.
*0b4k3 has made music for a Hyundai advertisement<ref>https://www.instagram.com/maxillajp/reel/C7fx9ZnPWQH/</ref>.
